<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
    <style>
        /* Email styles need to be inline */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .header {
            background-color: #f8f8f8;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #e7e7e7;
        }

        .content {
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .button {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        .logo {
            object-fit: cover;
        }

        .footer {
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding-top: 20px;
            border-top: 1px solid #e7e7e7;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #777;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #333;">
    <h2>New Login Detected</h2>
    <%= image_tag attachments["logo"].url, class: "logo", style:"height: 80px; display: block;",  alt: "Company Logo"  %>

    <p>Hello <%= @user.user_profile&.first_name || @user.email %>,</p>

    <p>We noticed a new login to your <strong>BitBridge Global</strong>:</p>



    <p>If this was you, no further action is needed.</p>

    <p>If you don’t recognize this activity, we recommend that you contanct support and review your account’s security settings.</p>

    <p>Thank you,<br />
        The BitBridge Global Team

    </p>
     
</body>

</html>